MATCH_TOOL: Agent
MATCH_PATTERN: superpowers:writing-plans|superpowers:executing-plans
ADVISORY: |
  You are about to write or execute a plan based on a spec or design.

  CRITICAL LEARNING — Plan drift:
  Plans often become narrower than the spec they're based on. The agent
  executing the plan focuses on what's easy to implement (infrastructure,
  files, configuration) and misses what's harder to quantify (patterns,
  meta-processes, self-improvement loops).

  This happened in the self-learning workflow design: the spec described:
  1. Advisory hooks (✓ built)
  2. Hierarchical knowledge structure (✓ partially built)
  3. Self-learning loop mechanism (✗ NOT built)
  4. Per-app .claude/ directories (✗ NOT built)
  5. Skill update process (✗ NOT built)
  6. Promotion path mechanism (✗ NOT built)
  7. Daily health check cadence (✗ NOT built)

  The plan covered #1-2 and was executed successfully, but didn't include
  #3-7. The agent didn't notice until the user caught the gap.

  BEFORE EXECUTING A PLAN:
  1. Read the full spec/design document
  2. Compare plan section-by-section against spec
  3. Call out any sections of the spec not in the plan
  4. Ask: "Is this section intentionally deferred, or is it a gap?"

  This is the same pattern the self-learning system was designed to catch.
  Agents should be the first line of defense against drift.
